am buffers an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"unlimited number of elements. You can also set the policy to buffer a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified number of oldest or newest elements.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"limit"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A custom closure that yields values to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"AsyncStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This closure receives an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AsyncStream.Continuation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance that it uses to provide elements to the stream and terminate the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stream when finished."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"build"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AsyncStream.Continuation"},{"type":"text","text":" received by the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"build"},{"type":"text","text":" closure is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"appropriate for use in concurrent contexts. It is thread safe to send and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"finish; all calls to the continuation are serialized. However, calling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this from multiple concurrent contexts could result in out-of-order"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delivery."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example shows an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AsyncStream"},{"type":"text","text":" created with this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"initializer that produces 100 random numbers on a one-second interval,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"yield(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" to deliver each 